<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA TREATMENT OF THE 'HILARY IN HIDING' CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re "Trail of Abuse in the Hilary Custody Case," by Howard Rosenberg (April 24), 
about the dispute between Dr. Elizabeth Morgan and her former husband, Dr. Eric 
Foretich: 
</P>
<P>
Rosenberg claims this "may be the most stunning case of abuse by the media. . . 
." He himself has made a contribution to that abuse. 
</P>
<P>
Nowhere does he address the central issue -- the (alleged) sexual molestation 
of 7-year-old Hilary. 
</P>
<P>
Morgan was forced to take her case to the media. 
</P>
<P>
Rosenberg inadvertently demonstrates why. While pooh-poohing the claims of 
sexual abuse by saying no court has upheld the allegation, he ignores that a 
court barred Foretich from seeing another daughter (from a previous marriage) 
after accusations of sexual molestation arose and he ignores other court 
findings in this area. 
</P>
<P>
I know of no woman who would have acted differently from Morgan in going 
public. 
</P>
<P>
MEGAN CALLAWAY, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
