<HEADLINE>
<P>
HISTORY OF LITHUANIAN NATIONALISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article by Frankel and Kux is very much like the articles which were 
printed by the Nazis in the 1930s. 
</P>
<P>
Then the mud was slung at the Jewish people. In this article it is slung at 
Lithuanians. Note the derogatory adjectives, the hateful tone, the distortion 
of facts and one-sided, broad generalizations which are used to arouse 
contempt. Hitler built the ghettos based on contempt. 
</P>
<P>
It is disgusting to think that a "historical writer" (Brian D. Kux) is capable 
of such bigotry. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Frankel and Mr. Kux, your writing is more suited to the 1930s. 
</P>
<P>
MELANIE MASKOLIUNAS 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
</P>
</TEXT>
