<HEADLINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON'S UNESCO BOYCOTT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congratulations on your editorial. I too, along with most Americans, have been 
deeply disappointed in UNESCO. 
</P>
<P>
The United Nations, which began on such an idealistic and optimistic note, has 
ended up anything but that. 
</P>
<P>
UNESCO, its "educational, scientific and cultural" organization, is just 
another example of good Western intentions corrupted and gone astray. 
</P>
<P>
Instead of the neutral organization working for world peace and understanding 
as originally envisioned, it has become a mere propaganda machine for the 
political and military aspirations of the communist and the totalitarian 
elements of the Third World. Along with this, anti-American and anti-Western 
attacks are common. 
</P>
<P>
As pointed out in your editorial, UNESCO is so blatantly anti-Israel and 
pro-Palestinian, that any credibility it may have once had in helping to bring 
peace to the Middle East has been apparently totally lost. 
</P>
<P>
Let's continue to support America's and the United Kingdom's decision to refuse 
financial support until the original purpose is re-established. 
</P>
<P>
IRVING E. FRIEDMAN 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
