<HEADLINE>
<P>
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG WITH A BORING BALLPARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I wish to clarify a statement Mike Reilley made in his story about baseball 
parks. 
</P>
<P>
While the Dodger Stadium cafeteria does have a varied menu and decent food, the 
ushers will allow only fans sitting in the expensive seats access to it. 
</P>
<P>
Two-thirds of the stadium has only one real food choice -- hot dogs that are 
burned on the outside and cold on the inside. I have been to more than a dozen 
stadiums, and Dodger Stadium ranks near the bottom in quality and is without 
question at the bottom in variety. 
</P>
<P>
An organization that draws 3 million people each year should do more for their 
fans. 
</P>
<P>
MIKE LORRAINE, Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
