<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRSICH WINS TWICE AT VENTURA RACEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Firsich of Port Hueneme won both the Street Stock and figure-eight main 
events at Ventura Raceway on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Griffin of Oxnard led the tightly contested 15-lap Street Stock main event 
until the final turn. 
</P>
<P>
Griffin, Don Green of Ventura and Dave Hume of Ventura all tangled high in Turn 
4 and Firsich cut underneath the careening cars to beat Griffin by a car 
length. Hume was third. 
</P>
<P>
Firsich moved within 10 points of the figure-eight season points leader, John 
Csorba of Oxnard, with a much easier victory in the 12-lap figure-eight main 
event. 
</P>
<P>
Firsich led wire-to-wire as Csorba missed the race because of a broken rear 
axle on his Monte Carlo. 
</P>
<P>
The break was sustained in an earlier heat race. 
</P>
<P>
Cory Kruseman of Ventura won his second consecutive 12-lap Mini-Stock 
figure-eight main event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
