<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
STUDEBAKER, HALL ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four singles players and two doubles teams from Moorpark College advanced into 
the quarterfinals of the Western State Conference men's individual tennis 
championships Friday at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Mike Studebaker led Moorpark, qualifying in singles and advancing 
with fellow singles qualifier Derek Hall in doubles. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark's Jeff Walendy and Andrew Van Cott also advanced in singles and as a 
doubles team. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce's Al Martinez, one of two No. 1-seeded players, and teammate Vince 
Brandt advanced into the round of 16 as did Glendale's Dun Cao and Ventura's 
Brant Brazill. 
</P>
<P>
Singles and doubles quarterfinalists qualify for the Southern California 
regionals of the state championships. 
</P>
<P>
In the WSC women's championships at Santa Barbara College, Moorpark's Elise 
Nakawatase posted a 6-0, 6-0 victory over Gina Montion of Ventura to advance to 
the quarterfinals in singles. 
</P>
<P>
Elise and her mother, Patti, won their doubles match as did Moorpark's Cathleen 
Clark and Amy Perry to earn spots in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale placed two players, Genoveva Guba and Claudia Boumann, in the round of 
16, and the doubles team of Boumann and Tracy Fabian in the final eight. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 7, Cal Lutheran 6 -- Down, 6-4, in the sixth 
inning, host Southern California College scored three runs on five walks and a 
hit batter to win the NAIA District 3 game. 
</P>
