<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Stereotypes," a short film co-produced by a California company and the Soviet 
Peace Committee in Moscow, will be screened Sunday at the Huntington Beach 
Church of Religious Science. 
</P>
<P>
The 25-minute film is a mix of live action and animation that explores common 
stereotypes about Soviets and Americans. American-Soviet teams were formed to 
write and animate the film, while Soviet musicians composed the score. 
</P>
<P>
Singer Cyndee Peters, who sings a number in "Stereotypes," will perform after 
the film's 2 p.m. screening. A voluntary donation will be asked for admission. 
The church is located at 2205 Main St. in Huntington Beach. Information: (714) 
969-1331. 
</P>
