METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TRUCK CRASH BLOCKS LANES ON BRIDGE FOR 2 
HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A big rig truck overturned east of the toll booths on the Vincent Thomas Bridge 
on Terminal Island Friday, blocking all westbound lanes for nearly two hours 
until the wreckage was removed. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the Terminal Island side of the bridge, which spans 
the Los Angeles Harbor to San Pedro. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
The truck and another vehicle collided at 2:45 p.m. on the road near Seaside 
Avenue, said Officer Harold Daily of the California Highway Patrol. All San 
Pedro-bound motorists were prevented from entering the bridge until the lanes 
were reopened about 4:30 p.m., Daily said. 
