<LENGTH>
<P>
69 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Danny Everett's time of 45.04 seconds for the indoor 400 meters in a meet at 
Stuttgart, West Germany, on Feb. 4 was rejected as a world record because the 
race had an improperly staggered start, the International Amateur Athletic 
Federation said. 
</P>
<P>
Everett's time bettered the world record of 45.05, set by East German Thomas 
Schoenlebe in 1988, but IAAF technical director Mike Gee said it can't be 
accepted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
