<P>
The family of a 19-year-old University of Florida baseball player who died 
March 17 from complications after shoulder surgery last March has hired an 
attorney to investigate the matter. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Georgiadis was kept alive on life support systems in intensive care for 
two days after surgery to tighten ligaments in his right shoulder. An autopsy 
has been performed and pathology experts have been consulted, but nobody has 
been able to explain his death. 
