</P>
<P>
EUROPE; 
</P>
<P>
FRANCE, BRITAIN MAP NEW SECURITY LINKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain and France, responding to President Bush's plan not to modernize 
short-range nuclear weapons in Europe, announced that they will forge closer 
links of their own in security and defense matters. This may include 
cooperation on their own nuclear weapons programs, aides said at a summit 
meeting in England of Britain's Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher and France's 
President Francois Mitterrand. Thatcher noted that the two are "independent 
nuclear deterrent powers -- the only two in Europe." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
