<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
HUSTLER CARTOONIST SENTENCED TO 6 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The cartoonist who created the Hustler magazine feature "Chester the Molester" 
has been sentenced to six years in prison for molesting a teen-age girl. 
</P>
<P>
Dwaine B. Tinsley, 44, of Simi Valley was convicted in January of five counts 
of sexually assaulting a 13-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
The Superior Court jury acquitted him on six additional sex charges involving 
the same girl but were deadlocked on five others, which were dismissed, Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Matthew J. Hardy said. 
</P>
<P>
Tinsley was known for his Hustler magazine cartoon series "Chester the 
Molester," which depicted an old man who is sexually attracted to children. 
</P>
<P>
Tinsley is free on $50,000 bail until Monday, when a hearing is scheduled to 
decide whether he can remain free while he appeals his case. 
</P>
