<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
$10,000 DUMP TRUCK DESTROYED IN FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ventura city dump truck worth about $10,000 was destroyed after catching fire 
in the city garage Friday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A sprinkler system in the City Maintenance Garage at Thompson Boulevard and 
Sanjon Road put out the fire after it started about 4:30 a.m., preventing 
significant damage to the building, Ventura Police Officer Diane McCaskill 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Smoke caused $500 worth of damage to the building, McCaskill said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was caused by an electrical short under the dashboard of the truck, 
which was being repaired, McCaskill said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
