<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
15-YEAR-OLD HELD IN THEFT OF ICE CREAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old ice cream vendor was beaten and robbed of 140 ice cream bars in 
Santa Paula, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Police took a 15-year-old girl into custody about 4:30 p.m. Thursday after 
discovering the vendor's cart turned over in her front yard and the bars 
stuffed in her freezer, Santa Paula Police Cmdr. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Gonzales said. 
</P>
<P>
The vendor, from La Tapatia Ice Cream of San Bernardino, was hawking the snacks 
from his pushcart on Pleasant Street when two males and a teen-age girl beat 
him and ran off with his cart, Gonzales said. 
</P>
<P>
The vendor's name is not being released because he is a minor, a Police 
Department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The vendor, badly shaken by the experience, told police that he had been "hit 
all over," Gonzales said. But he did not require medical attention and was not 
taken to a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
No money was taken. The robbers were after only the frozen goods, Gonzales 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Police discovered the cart on its side in front of the girl's house about a 
block away on Walnut Street, Gonzales said. 
</P>
<P>
Police are searching for the two males, believed to be juveniles, Gonzales 
said. 
</P>
