BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agency Quits Perrier: The San Francisco firm Hal Riney &amp; Partners, which 
until recently created virtually all the ads for the troubled Perrier Group, 
has resigned the account in which it created ads for several Perrier-owned 
brands, including Arrowhead drinking water and Calistoga Sparkling Mineral 
Water. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the agency was fired from the $5-million account that 
created ads for Perrier Sparkling Mineral Water. "Perrier has been breaking up 
the account into a lot of pieces," said John Yost, general manager at the 
agency. "It seemed a good time to leave." 
</P>
