<P>
23 KURDISH REBELS DIE IN CLASHES WITH TURK FORCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANKARA, Turkey 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Government forces killed 23 suspected Kurdish guerrillas in two clashes in 
southeastern and eastern Turkey, the Anatolia news agency reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The dispatch said three village guards were also killed during the fighting 
Thursday. 
</P>
