<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACTIVITIES FOR BE KIND TO ANIMALS WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETSY S. SIINO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here are a few activities that celebrate the 75th annual National Be Kind to 
Animals Week, which kicks off Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
* Pet Parade: Bring your pet or pets (on leashes or in carriers) to the Pet 
Parade sponsored by the Los Angeles SPCA and KRTH radio Sunday in Century City. 
</P>
<P>
The parade will follow the Avenue of the Stars route in front of the ABC 
Entertainment Complex from 1 p.m. to 3 p.m.; check-in time is 11 a.m. The entry 
fee is $10 per animal, which includes a commemorative T-shirt and participation 
award. Proceeds benefit Los Angeles SPCA and Caring for Babies With AIDS. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call the Los Angeles SPCA, (213) 730-5300, or KRTH, (213) 
937-5230. 
</P>
<P>
* Blessing of the Animals: On Sunday (also known as Humane Sunday), Pomona 
Valley Humane Society will hold a Blessing of the Animals at 2 p.m. Father 
William Easterling of St. Joseph's Church in Pomona will officiate at the 
Pomona Valley Humane Society animal shelter, 500 Humane Way, Pomona. All 
animals must be restrained. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call Pomona Valley Humane Society, (714) 623-9777. 
</P>
<P>
* An Animal Affair: To get an early start on Be Kind to Animals Week, attend 
"An Animal Affair" at the Orange County Animal Shelter in Orange, today from 10 
a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Board of Supervisors has also waived all fees for animals 
adopted on this day (with the exception of vaccination fees, licensing fees and 
the refundable spay or neuter deposits). Each new pet owner will receive a pet 
starter kit for each adopted pet. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Animal Shelter is at 561 City Drive South, Orange. For more 
information, call (714) 834-6943. 
</P>
<P>
* Festival for the Animals: Animal lovers in San Diego can check out the 
Festival for the Animals, sponsored by the San Diego Humane Society and SPCA 
Sunday in the Nautilus Amphitheater at Sea World. 
</P>
<P>
Admission to the park buys you admission to the festival, which will include 
three special shows at 11:30 a.m., 1 p.m. and 3:30 p.m. For more information, 
call the San Diego Humane Society and SPCA, (619) 299-7012. BETSY S. SIINO 
</P>
</TEXT>
