<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
ROSEMEAD MAN IS KILLED IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVAN MAHARAJ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Rosemead man was killed when his car collided with a pickup truck in Los 
Alamitos, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Chen, 25, died at Long Beach Memorial Hospital at 7:04 p.m. Thursday, 
about two hours after he was airlifted by helicopter from the crash scene. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos Police Cpl. Rod McKenzie said an initial investigation determined 
that Chen tried to make a left turn as he was leaving his workplace on Los 
Vaqueros Circle. 
</P>
<P>
Chen failed to yield the right of way and his Toyota station wagon was rammed 
by an oncoming Ford pickup, McKenzie said. 
</P>
<P>
McKenzie said Chen died from massive head, chest and abdominal injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The crash was the first fatal traffic accident in Los Alamitos since October, 
1986, police said. DAVAN MAHARAJ 
</P>
</TEXT>
