<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL APPROVES NEW HOUSING PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THANHTHUY NGUYEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved a new housing plan that calls for the 
construction of at least 48 housing units over the next five years. 
</P>
<P>
The state-mandated plan, which must be revised every five years, also calls for 
saving 20 existing affordable housing units and rehabilitating five other 
existing housing units. 
</P>
<P>
City planners prepared the study by examining population and employment trends 
in La Palma to come up with a strategy for meeting local housing needs. The 
plan includes an assessment of the city's housing stock, a listing of all 
undeveloped land in the city, a statement of the city's housing goals and 
policies, and provisions for enough affordable housing. THANHTHUY NGUYEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HOUSING -- ORANGE COUNTY; LA PALMA (CA) -- DEVELOPMENT AND REDEVELOPMENT; 
AFFORDABLE HOUSING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050590-0151 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 215181 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 5, 1990, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
